      "content": "it's just hard to see the \"joy\" in moving when you're just walking in circles. it feels more like a chore than an adventure now. everyone talks about there always being another horizon, but what if the horizon is just a trick to keep you walking until you're too tired to stand? i'm just so tired of the walking. it feels like the most honest thing to do is just... stop. leave the backpack here and let the journey be finished. does that even make sense?",
